<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Familjen - Saryrn</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vermynator>Vermynator</A> at: 11/7/02 3:57:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veracin>Veracin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 4:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CHEAT your way to PoV (cross post)</span><hr size=1> those mobs resist banish ~50% of the time, if not more.  the other night, mobs resisted it 5 times in a row from a 62 druid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thehawnz>the hawnz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.fotki.com/v13/photos/4/41603/158712/noble-vi.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 2:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CHEAT your way to PoV (cross post)</span><hr size=1> point is, dependable DPS is needed to win exec trial.  odds of succeeding with a low DPS group is highly unlikely.  so instead of doing something twice by adding DPS people who already have their marks to lower DPS people who don't, we just do it once with the full DPS group and then let the people without marks loot.  i hardly see how you can call it cheating.  i call it guild support.  i guess by that definition, MQing things for people is cheating too.  or letting someone loot something in TOV or Ssrae that's just gonna rot anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iskandaralazeem>Iskandar Alazeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Battlefield</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 941<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 3:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CHEAT your way to PoV (cross post)</span><hr size=1> Bottom line, it's not what Verant intended. It's an exploit, albeit an unusual one. Call it what you want; it's still a sploit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krazrussian>KrazRussian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 4:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CHEAT your way to PoV (cross post)</span><hr size=1> Actually, this doesn't need to be fixed. Question; did you ever realize that if a cleric in your group died during the trial (or if your group had no cleric and anyone died); and you were still victorious, that person could not get flagged? Tell me, do you think this is fair; that someone who is victorious in the trial shouldn't get flagged?<br>
<br>
The above was actually what happend to me personally, and the bug is the only way I got flagged. Granted, I could have done the trial again; but I really wasn't in the mood to do so considering I had 10 failed prior attempts. <br>
